    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a concours-level 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a definitive example of high-revving naturally aspirated engineering. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been meticulously calibrated. This unit features a reinforced rear subframe and updated rod bearings, addressing critical preventative maintenance points for the E46 chassis. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a limited-slip variable M differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec with fresh bushings and OEM Sachs dampers, providing the tactile feedback and lateral stability expected of a flagship M-car. The exterior finish is original and free of imperfections, while the cabin retains its structural integrity with no signs of bolster fatigue or electronic pixel failure. This is a mechanically synchronized specimen for the collector who values technical purity.",
      "price": 46500.0,
